Description: Corroded copper alloy fitting made of a thin almond-shaped and curved strip of metal, with a long central slot. One pointed end has been cut longitudinally, and the tips of the two sides overlap;the function of the item remains undetermined, possibly a kind of grommet.
Curator's comments: The Museum register indicates a general reference to the small bronze finds mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 ( § 80), but the item is not clearly described.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.80, p.186, pl.28)
